    "interpretation": "Paper 38 Remark after Lemma L3 states C_3(n_max) <= sup_{N <= n_max} sqrt((N-1)/(N+1)).  Paper 38's Berezin map (eq:B_def) restricts to N <= n_max by Plancherel cutoff, so on Berezin images Paper 38 is correct.  But Paper 38 does NOT operate on the natural-substrate envelope N <= 2 n_max - 1; the natural-substrate-side L3 bound is moot for Paper 38's Riemannian propinquity assembly (which lives only on Berezin images via the tunneling pair).  The envelope erratum is a Paper 45 issue: Paper 45's natural substrate sees the larger envelope through the chirality-doubled multiplier algebra.",
